headline: South Korea’s Yoon Survives Impeachment After Martial Law Fiasco
summary: (Bloomberg) -- South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol survived impeachment on Saturday as his ruling party refused to join an opposition bid to oust him after he shocked the nation and its allies by briefly declaring martial law.
